Description: Rim and wall sherd of East Greek (Late Wild Goat?) pottery krater; pale brown clay with much silver mica; glaze fired orange; cream slip; exterior, glaze remains; dots on outer edge of rim; interior glazed; remains of painted meander running right on rim; inscription cut through meander.
Curator's comments: Is from just to the left of 1888,0601.708a
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.781)
